1
00:00:00,267 --> 00:00:03,033
[Would you like to join Spirit Fingers?]

2
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:25,609
♫ A heart that remains
unchanged through time ♫

3
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:31,100
♫ Our eternal story
that will last forever ♫

4
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,363
[This drama is fictional, and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

5
00:00:37,387 --> 00:00:40,227
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

6
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,600
Thank you.

7
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:03,033
- Song U Yeon.
- Yes?

8
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,000
You got this!

9
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,576
I hate presentation time
more than anything in the world.

10
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:24,243
What if my voice shakes too much?

11
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:25,443
What if my voice cracks?

12
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:27,533
What if the kids laugh at me?

13
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,033
But the hardest thing of it

14
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,200
are the stares of all those eyes
focused solely on me.

15
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:44,809
Yet, here I am,

16
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:47,900
somehow standing here

17
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:52,509
modeling for an art class.

18
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:55,300
In the middle of Hongdae, no less.

19
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,709
So this is

20
00:01:57,733 --> 00:02:00,143
the most monumental event

21
00:02:00,167 --> 00:02:03,267
of my eighteen-year-old life.

22
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,143
Good!

23
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:32,176
Okay, good!

24
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,143
Ye Rim enters. Ye Rim!

25
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:35,967
Perfect!

26
00:02:38,848 --> 00:02:42,272
[Episode 1]

27
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,043
Okay, good!

28
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,209
Great! Now without Gi Jeong.

29
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:50,843
Ye Rim, stay just like that.

30
00:02:50,867 --> 00:02:52,767
Solo shot!

31
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:56,376
We'll go solo.

32
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,876
Good! Okay.

33
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,176
Don't make that face!

34
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,309
Stay still for a second.

35
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:06,176
- Stop taking photos.
- Just one more.

36
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,609
Got it! We got it!

37
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:09,043
Wait.

38
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:10,276
I said stop it, please!

39
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:12,576
Let's take proper photos.

40
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:15,943
Every photo of you makes
our followers skyrocket.

41
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:19,276
Gi Jeong, if you're gonna
make that face, give it to me.

42
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,277
Are you done?

43
00:03:20,301 --> 00:03:22,943
No. Ten minutes break.

44
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:26,043
Gi Jeong, why are you so on point today?

45
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:29,500
I always look best in
couple shots with you.

46
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,343
Where are you going?

47
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:37,209
Where are you going?

48
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:39,909
Hey! Where are you going? We're not done.

49
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:42,033
Taking a dump.

50
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:46,543
At least my bowls are
longer than that punk's.

51
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:48,400
I'm better than him.

52
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,100
[Dae O tagged Gi Jeong in a post]

53
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:56,400
I told him not to post my face!

54
00:03:57,867 --> 00:04:00,209
You're dead.

55
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:02,509
I came too early.

56
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:05,276
I'm just going around.

57
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,876
Mi Rae is almost here. You?

58
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,643
Ten minutes?

59
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:12,300
Alright, let's meet at the coffee shop.

60
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:22,876
Wow!

61
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:25,533
Who actually wears this?

62
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,800
Beautiful.

63
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:34,776
Beautiful.

64
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:38,133
What do these people eat to look so pretty?

65
00:04:41,767 --> 00:04:45,500
Ever considered being pretty by not eating?

66
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:56,209
Look at these outfits.

67
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,376
Ugh, so dull!

68
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,443
[Delulu] She's the Delulu.

69
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:02,876
Everyone has one.

70
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:04,976
But not all skinny people are equal.

71
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,467
[Delusional Ego]
That's my delusional self talking.

72
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:14,443
You're not elegantly slim.

73
00:05:14,467 --> 00:05:15,643
Look.

74
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:18,376
There's no hope for shapeless,
petite skinniness like yours.

75
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,343
Two years until college.

76
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:24,367
I think your growth plates are still open.

77
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,409
Press your back against the wall,

78
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,809
center your weight in your abdomen,

79
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:36,733
and touch your big toe first when stepping.

80
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:41,443
They say that can add
up to 3cm to your height.

81
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:42,476
Wait.

82
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,876
Shouldn't you focus
on something else first?

83
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,409
Oh, right!

84
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:51,200
I need to get into college first.

85
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:53,809
Hey, what's that?

86
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,633
- Huh?
- What is it?

87
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,743
Not done yet?

88
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:09,876
Only one minute passed.

89
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,643
She suggested the punishment idea.

90
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:13,076
Darn it!

91
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:15,733
If you move again and we will add poses.

92
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:18,576
You moved again.

93
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,709
Add a pose.

94
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:22,143
Okay.

95
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:24,643
Since we're here,

96
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:27,367
draw to your heart's content!

97
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:32,433
Thank you.

98
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,309
The drawing is coming better today.

99
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:40,309
I'm nervous with so many people watching.

100
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,843
Wow, the drawing actually got smaller.

101
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,776
Pretend nobody's watching and draw.

102
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:47,733
Or enjoy the attention like I do.

103
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:03,943
Wow!

104
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:06,700
He's so handsome.

105
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,576
Oh, no!

106
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,733
Was I staring too obviously?

107
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:27,909
No! Don't fall, don't fall!

108
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:29,743
- Excuse me!
- Huh?

109
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:31,876
Huh?

110
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:35,376
Sorry. Do you have a moment?

111
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,200
Huh?

112
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,609
Me?

113
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:42,376
What's this about?

114
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,509
Is this what they call being hit on?

115
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:48,343
This is a drawing club.
Would you like to join us?

116
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:50,009
But this guy...

117
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,576
He looks even hotter up close.

118
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,943
How is his face so perfectly small?

119
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:57,509
How are his eyes, nose, and lips
so perfectly proportioned?

120
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:58,643
Wow, look at his skin.

121
00:07:58,667 --> 00:08:01,276
There's no need to feel pressured.

122
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:04,043
And why does his voice
have to sound like that...

123
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:05,743
Why would someone like him

124
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:09,233
ask someone like me for the time?

125
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:12,967
Could it be...

126
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:15,767
Maybe...

127
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:18,909
Just maybe...

128
00:08:18,933 --> 00:08:21,800
Is spring finally coming for me too

129
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:29,043
for the first time in my 18 years?

130
00:08:29,067 --> 00:08:31,676
Just three minutes. Three minutes.
Three minutes, you know?

131
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:35,400
Huh? What three minutes...

132
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,143
Our outfits might look strange to you.

133
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:41,343
Just stand still like this for three minutes.

134
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:42,376
We're not asking you to dance

135
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,243
or perform a talent show.

136
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,267
Just stand still.

137
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:05,043
♫ Nothing special, wherever I look ♫

138
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:10,376
♫ My ordinary days
with nothing remarkable ♫

139
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:15,676
♫ Changed completely when you appeared ♫

140
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:20,376
♫ Everything about me keeps transforming ♫

141
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,300
Where did she go? She's
not answering the calls.

142
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,976
Huh?

143
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,909
Isn't that Song over there?

144
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,843
- Where? Where?
- There.

145
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,843
Huh?

146
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:35,300
I want to disappear.

147
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:40,309
He is so serious.

148
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:43,676
I can't back out now,
it's too late to refuse.

149
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:47,700
I must be crazy. No
matter how stunning he is.

150
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,376
She's completely frozen.

151
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,976
You can see how nervous she is.

152
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,576
Her shoulders will hurt later.

153
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,776
She's super tense.

154
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,543
Reminds me of when you first modeled.

155
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:04,167
We thought you were a wooden doll.

156
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,243
Fighting!

157
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:13,409
- Fighting!
- Don't change your posture.

158
00:10:13,433 --> 00:10:14,676
I'm sorry.

159
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,276
What is she doing there?

160
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,509
Hey, Song...

161
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,433
Stay still.

162
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:22,876
Hey, hey, hey!

163
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:25,009
Where did you find
such a cute and nice girl?

164
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:27,976
Koo Seon Ho has skills.

165
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,800
Right? She's adorable.

166
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,576
But I'm just wondering.

167
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,433
Yeah?

168
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:38,276
Why are you still wearing that?

169
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:40,476
What?

170
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,743
- This.
- Come on.

171
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:44,009
You should've told me earlier.

172
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:45,833
You did it on purpose, right?

173
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:49,676
Wow!

174
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,676
She is a goddess.

175
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,309
Hey, look.

176
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:54,809
Any marks left?

177
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:56,176
Perfect good-looking couple.

178
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,843
No, it's fine.

179
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:58,909
Hey, there are!

180
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:00,509
Want to die? You wanna die?

181
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:02,943
They look good together.

182
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:06,276
Ugh, it's cold.

183
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,409
You're cold, right?

184
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:08,743
Just two more minutes.

185
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:10,243
No, I'm not cold.

186
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:13,267
Silly, you're freezing.

187
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:17,076
You look prettier when still.

188
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:19,143
You look mischievous when smiling.

189
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:22,443
How does the mood keep
shifting so dramatically?

190
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:24,609
I look like a complete mess today.

191
00:11:24,633 --> 00:11:26,909
I should've taken off my glasses.

192
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:30,009
Ah, I just want to go home.

193
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:33,009
Ugh, why are three minutes so long?

194
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:35,400
Can't I just close my eyes?

195
00:11:36,633 --> 00:11:37,676
I'm sorry.

196
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,867
You're sorry?

197
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,743
[Heart Fluttering]

198
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:46,109
[Girl with Delayed Heart-fluttering]

199
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:48,776
That's exactly

200
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,776
the lip-pursing technique they talk about.

201
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,109
Suddenly I'm not cold anymore.

202
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:56,676
I could stand for three hours.

203
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:58,709
No, 300 years?

204
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:01,467
I could endure even 3,000 years.

205
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:06,309
I want to take off those glasses.

206
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:09,709
Just once. I really want
to take them off just once.

207
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:11,809
Okay, three minutes are up.

208
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,643
Good work, cutie.

209
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:15,600
Thank you for your hard work.

210
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:19,476
This is for you.

211
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,367
Honey.

212
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:26,100
Your poses were really cool today.

213
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:30,243
You have such captivating eyes.

214
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:32,609
You did well.

215
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:33,876
See you again, cutie.

216
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,867
Hey, watch the tail.

217
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:42,476
Hey, Song, what was this?

218
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,400
Who are those people?

219
00:12:45,067 --> 00:12:48,533
They said it's a drawing club.

220
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,909
Hey, is this you?

221
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:55,009
Wasn't it a gathering for
people who like drawing?

222
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:56,010
What is this?

223
00:12:56,034 --> 00:12:59,543
To be precise, it's a gathering
for people who enjoy drawing.

224
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:01,743
Wow, he's ridiculously good-looking.

225
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:06,076
We gather because we enjoy it,
even if we're not great at it.

226
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:07,576
Sounds fun.

227
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,643
- Does it seem fun to you?
- Huh?

228
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:12,676
Then will you come to
next week's gathering?

229
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:15,867
Contact me if you're interested.

230
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:22,009
What's your name?

231
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:23,809
What?

232
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:26,109
Song... U Yeon.

233
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:28,667
Ah, U Yeon.

234
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,676
I'll remember your name.

235
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,600
See you around.

236
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:36,376
Hey, Koo Seon Ho, hurry up!

237
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,209
He said he'd remember.

238
00:13:39,233 --> 00:13:41,176
Whoa! This is a total game-changer!

239
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:44,276
[Koo Seon Ho] Hey, what? Song
U Yeon, how did you pull this off?

240
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:47,400
How did you do it, Song U Yeon?

241
00:13:55,267 --> 00:14:00,409
Even someone insignificant
like Song U Yeon gets hit on.

242
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:02,676
Then why...

243
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:06,167
Why have I been alive
for 18 years? Seriously!

244
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,143
Isn't that guy

245
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:12,600
- from some kind of cult?
- Must be your wishful thinking.

246
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:16,433
Will you call?

247
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:18,743
I'm not sure.

248
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:20,643
I don't know what to do.

249
00:14:20,667 --> 00:14:21,676
Oh, right!

250
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:22,709
You're really bad at drawing.

251
00:14:22,733 --> 00:14:23,909
I used to draw well when I was younger.

252
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,076
That's hilarious!

253
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,876
I was way better at drawing
than you in kindergarten.

254
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,309
Stop lying.

255
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:29,809
That's not true. I was good at it.

256
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,209
So give this to me.

257
00:14:31,233 --> 00:14:34,276
You won't call anyway.

258
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,576
I'll do it when I get home.

259
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,267
Where are you going? Do it now.

260
00:14:40,067 --> 00:14:42,800
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

261
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:48,809
How long will you keep hesitating?

262
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:51,309
Give me a moment, okay? Let me think.

263
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,509
Will he really remember my name?

264
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:55,743
Just saying... What if I called
without reading the mood?

265
00:14:55,767 --> 00:14:59,100
Yeom Se, I can't do this.

266
00:14:59,963 --> 00:15:01,143
Come on.

267
00:15:01,167 --> 00:15:03,509
The first time is always hard.

268
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:05,509
Take a deep breath.

269
00:15:05,533 --> 00:15:09,500
Breathe in, and breathe out.

270
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:12,033
Breathe in.

271
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,209
Breathe out.

272
00:15:15,233 --> 00:15:17,276
- Breathe in...
- Look at this.

273
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,443
Hey!

274
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:20,833
Hey! Call! Call!

275
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:24,709
Did he answer? Not yet?

276
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:26,667
Hello?

277
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,476
- Hello?
- Ugh, so frustrating!

278
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,609
Oh, yes.

279
00:15:33,633 --> 00:15:36,009
It's the pretty girl who modeled earlier.

280
00:15:36,033 --> 00:15:37,409
Why did you call me "pretty girl"?

281
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:39,276
What?

282
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:42,509
Ah, Song U Yeon.

283
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:45,667
He really remembered.

284
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:48,376
- Hello?
- Oh, yes.

285
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:51,143
Yes, this is Song U Yeon. How can I help?

286
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:52,643
Thank you for calling.

287
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:55,409
So you were interested
in drawing after all.

288
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:58,509
Ah, yes. That's true, but...

289
00:15:58,533 --> 00:16:00,243
But still

290
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:02,176
I'm really not good at it.

291
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,609
And it's been ages since I drew.

292
00:16:03,633 --> 00:16:05,309
You like drawing, right?

293
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,943
Liking it is enough.

294
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:11,009
It doesn't matter if you're good or bad.

295
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:15,233
It doesn't... matter?

296
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:23,976
Hey, what's did she
say? Is she coming or not?

297
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,609
She keeps hesitating.

298
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:27,209
Hesitating?

299
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:29,509
Right. Exactly our style.

300
00:16:29,533 --> 00:16:30,876
We picked the wrong front person.

301
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:34,067
I should've stepped up and pulled her in
with sisterly charm.

302
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:38,133
Then just pull her in.

303
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:45,676
[Koo Seon Ho:
You've been invited to Spirit Fingers]

304
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,276
- Spirit Fingers?
- Spirit Fingers?

305
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:49,743
[Spirit Fingers: A
group for croquis lovers]

306
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:51,109
[Would you like to accept the membership?]

307
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:52,776
We meet every Sunday.

308
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:54,243
If you accept the invitation,

309
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:58,976
I'll message you this
week's location and time.

310
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,843
You're not fooling around, are you?

311
00:17:01,867 --> 00:17:03,767
What do you mean?

312
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:09,109
U Yeon, close the fridge.

313
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:12,833
Stop messing around and study, okay?

314
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,943
Just do well on your midterms
this time, understood?

315
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:18,767
Okay.

316
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:26,867
Ugh, it smells.

317
00:17:41,933 --> 00:17:45,367
[Searching] Spirit Fingers.

318
00:17:50,033 --> 00:17:53,000
These kids have confidence.

319
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:59,343
They have themes and dress codes
for every gathering?

320
00:17:59,367 --> 00:18:03,743
[Beware of colds! Dress code:
Patients, nurses, doctors, hospital]

321
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:05,843
[Koo Seon Ho]

322
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:08,043
He's an art student.

323
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,143
That explains it.

324
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,443
[Shaking]

325
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:12,076
[Course registration successful!]

326
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,143
[Amidst swaying cherry blossoms]

327
00:18:13,167 --> 00:18:16,176
[Your strokes are a bit heavy]

328
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,343
[Let's nail this project too]

329
00:18:18,367 --> 00:18:20,709
Are they dating?

330
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:23,243
[Suddenly in selfie mode]

331
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:26,300
[Our grades are in your hands]
They look great together.

332
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:30,400
They go to the same school.

333
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,176
Liking it is enough.

334
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:39,533
It doesn't matter if you're good or bad.

335
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,143
Ah, U Yeon.

336
00:19:19,167 --> 00:19:21,243
I'll remember your name.

337
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:24,500
Since you actually remembered it,

338
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,809
okay!

339
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:32,209
I just need to ace the midterms.

340
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:35,593
[Spirit Fingers: A group for croquis lovers
Would you like to accept the membership?]

341
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:39,067
[Yes]

342
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:46,667
[Welcome! This Sunday at 3PM
at Dadada Cafe near Hongdae]

343
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:05,033
[Spirit Fingers, First Meeting]

344
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:09,700
The breeze is nice.

345
00:20:10,567 --> 00:20:11,843
Close the window.

346
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:14,367
My hair will get messed up.

347
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:18,243
Why this sudden library-level quietness?

348
00:20:18,267 --> 00:20:19,343
You think you can study together?

349
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:21,709
Bad students always
flaunt their study sessions.

350
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:25,776
Look at your brother. He studied at home and
still got into Seoul National University.

351
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,209
Here we go again.

352
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:29,643
Stop comparing me to a
cheat code guy like him.

353
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:31,743
I'm a victim of genetic favoritism.

354
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:32,744
Don't worry.

355
00:20:32,768 --> 00:20:35,543
If you get into SNU like him, I'll pay
for double eyelid surgery and a nose job.

356
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:38,443
We will work on your posture.
I'll get you a personal trainer.

357
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:42,476
Why do you always hunch like an old lady?

358
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,243
Square those shoulders.

359
00:20:44,267 --> 00:20:46,643
Straighten your back.

360
00:20:46,667 --> 00:20:49,643
Yep, I am your real mom.

361
00:20:49,667 --> 00:20:52,009
Moms who only say 'Pretty girl! Good job!'

362
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:53,376
ruin their kids.

363
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,976
Self-awareness is crucial.

364
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,909
Se Ra's top of her
school, no worries there.

365
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:59,609
Mi Rae is the problem.

366
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:01,843
Hang out with people beneficial to you.

367
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:03,443
Even friends have tiers.

368
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:04,444
Mom!

369
00:21:04,468 --> 00:21:06,909
Do you think friendships last forever?

370
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:10,333
You go to different colleges
and watch them crumble.

371
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,543
See you later.

372
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,143
Come back early. Dad's been moody lately.

373
00:21:19,167 --> 00:21:22,009
Check your messages.

374
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:23,643
Where's your hairband?

375
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,667
It's in my bag.

376
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:31,209
Tie your hair up properly.

377
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:33,609
Covering acne makes it worse.

378
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:36,667
Stop procrastinating and study.

379
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,243
- Does it look like dog eyes?
- No, it's pretty.

380
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:09,609
I almost popped my
eye out putting these in.

381
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:11,643
Wow, ditching class
and wearing contacts for a guy?

382
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:13,576
- Total slacker behavior.
- That's not it!

383
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,643
I told you I'm going to draw.

384
00:22:14,667 --> 00:22:16,509
- Oh, drawing a guy?
- Seriously, no!

385
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:18,333
A worthwhile review.

386
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:36,033
Ugh, what a weirdo!

387
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:47,433
- Hey, grab her!
- Hey!

388
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:54,667
Get up.

389
00:22:58,633 --> 00:23:00,243
Hey!

390
00:23:00,267 --> 00:23:02,043
You glared at me?

391
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:03,309
No.

392
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:04,709
No?

393
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:07,567
Are you calling me a liar?

394
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:10,676
What's this?

395
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:11,843
You're wearing contacts?

396
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:13,443
You're so bad at makeup.

397
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:14,843
First time wearing makeup?

398
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:16,376
Did you follow a tutorial?

399
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,377
Hey!

400
00:23:17,401 --> 00:23:19,176
Like drawing stripes on a watermelon.

401
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,943
- Watermelon?
- Pumpkin!

402
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:25,076
Whatever, no difference.

403
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:29,643
When someone is talking,
you should look at them.

404
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:32,109
You just glared at me again, didn't you?

405
00:23:32,133 --> 00:23:34,843
No, I was just looking.

406
00:23:34,867 --> 00:23:36,609
Exactly.

407
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:40,233
Why the heck were you
staring at me like that, brat?

408
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:46,133
Because your lip tint looked pretty.

409
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:48,009
She said the lip tint is pretty.

410
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:50,009
Oh, pretty?

411
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:51,309
Want to try some on yours too?

412
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:52,943
I'll apply it nicely for you.

413
00:23:52,967 --> 00:23:54,209
- Wait!
- Hey, grab her!

414
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,009
Stay still, please.

415
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:58,776
Shut your mouth so I can apply it properly.

416
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:02,776
Hey, stay still or you'll get hurt.

417
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:04,609
Ever since I was young,

418
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:07,309
whenever I tried something new,

419
00:24:07,333 --> 00:24:10,643
I always made mistakes,
whether big or small.

420
00:24:10,667 --> 00:24:13,476
When using new crayons for the first time,

421
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:16,500
when first trying jump rope,

422
00:24:17,667 --> 00:24:19,576
- When starting a new semester...
- Why are you home at this hour?

423
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,533
You peed again?

424
00:24:25,233 --> 00:24:27,043
My stomach hurts.

425
00:24:27,067 --> 00:24:28,509
On my first high school exam day...

426
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:31,143
So will you take the college entrance exam?

427
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:33,976
Maybe it'll be fine if I
study for another year.

428
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,943
Sounds like a good idea.

429
00:24:35,967 --> 00:24:37,643
Did you think I'd say that?

430
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:40,109
Hey, Song U Yeon!

431
00:24:40,133 --> 00:24:43,976
Did you think I would be happy
if you said you're retaking the exam?

432
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,967
Just try retaking the exam, huh?

433
00:24:48,933 --> 00:24:50,643
Take good care of me.

434
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:51,943
Why is she like that?

435
00:24:51,967 --> 00:24:53,343
They said she got new indoor shoes.

436
00:24:53,367 --> 00:24:58,209
I used to be so careful
that my friends would tease me about it.

437
00:24:58,233 --> 00:25:00,909
But today I was so excited

438
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:04,076
that I forgot all the first-time experiences

439
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:07,133
required extra caution,

440
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:11,000
and completely forgot everything.

441
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:17,433
- Now, one, two, three...
- Two, three.

442
00:25:18,233 --> 00:25:19,909
Do you like it, Miss?

443
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,176
Oh my god, a goddess appears.

444
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,209
Awesome!

445
00:25:23,233 --> 00:25:24,509
Can I post this on InStar?

446
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:26,843
- Hey, take it, take it!
- Lift your chin.

447
00:25:26,867 --> 00:25:28,443
Smile a little.

448
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:31,176
I even used expensive
products. This won't do.

449
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:33,076
What? You don't like it?

450
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,609
Hey!

451
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:36,043
They said the others already arrived.

452
00:25:36,067 --> 00:25:37,933
Let's go.

453
00:25:38,667 --> 00:25:40,209
Consider yourself lucky.

454
00:25:40,233 --> 00:25:42,876
Watch where you look next time.

455
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,733
And buy some decent clothes.

456
00:25:52,533 --> 00:25:53,643
What a relief.

457
00:25:53,667 --> 00:25:55,967
I thought I was gonna die from fear...

458
00:25:57,867 --> 00:25:59,976
Relief?

459
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:03,076
You call this situation a relief?

460
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:06,843
What's there to be relieved about?
You coward! You idiot!

461
00:26:06,867 --> 00:26:09,133
Moron, scaredy-cat.

462
00:26:21,533 --> 00:26:23,176
Give it to me.

463
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,000
Huh?

464
00:26:25,733 --> 00:26:27,800
I said give it to me.

465
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:33,243
What the heck is happening today?

466
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:36,576
This is too much. What
did I even do wrong...

467
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,476
[Nam Gi Jeong] Huh?

468
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,009
That uniform

469
00:26:40,033 --> 00:26:41,876
belongs to the infamous Chiwon High.

470
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,833
Darn it.

471
00:26:44,967 --> 00:26:47,433
This is all I have! Seriously!

472
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,377
My tissues.

473
00:26:53,401 --> 00:26:55,200
Wait!

474
00:26:58,848 --> 00:27:00,992
Shoot.

475
00:27:05,033 --> 00:27:06,900
Wait?

476
00:27:11,867 --> 00:27:13,743
[Restroom]

477
00:27:13,767 --> 00:27:16,809
Why isn't he coming
out? Should I just leave?

478
00:27:16,833 --> 00:27:19,909
Yeah, he's a stranger
anyway. Let's just go.

479
00:27:19,933 --> 00:27:22,809
But he told me to wait.

480
00:27:22,833 --> 00:27:24,309
And you wait just because he said to?

481
00:27:24,333 --> 00:27:25,843
Why would he ask me to wait?

482
00:27:25,867 --> 00:27:27,109
Wait?

483
00:27:27,133 --> 00:27:28,209
Or not?

484
00:27:28,233 --> 00:27:29,576
Wait?

485
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:30,776
Or not?

486
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:33,367
This is driving me crazy!

487
00:27:38,567 --> 00:27:41,543
What? You actually waited?

488
00:27:41,567 --> 00:27:43,709
What?

489
00:27:43,733 --> 00:27:45,900
You told me to wait.

490
00:27:50,900 --> 00:27:52,043
Are you stupid?

491
00:27:52,067 --> 00:27:54,843
Hey, just because someone says wait,
you actually wait? Wow, unbelievable.

492
00:27:54,867 --> 00:27:57,233
Who even does that?

493
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,333
Hey.

494
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,243
Are you glaring at me now?

495
00:28:05,267 --> 00:28:07,900
I am just looking normally.

496
00:28:12,300 --> 00:28:14,800
Better than crying like a baby.

497
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:18,509
What?

498
00:28:18,533 --> 00:28:19,909
Hey,

499
00:28:19,933 --> 00:28:23,309
do you know the most
important thing in a fight?

500
00:28:23,333 --> 00:28:26,309
It's the staring contest.

501
00:28:26,333 --> 00:28:28,267
Staring contest?

502
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:32,176
Win the eye battle
and you've half-won already. Got it?

503
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:35,267
First, get rid of your pupils.

504
00:28:35,967 --> 00:28:38,767
How do I get rid of them?

505
00:28:39,833 --> 00:28:42,209
Like this!

506
00:28:42,233 --> 00:28:44,676
[Disappearance of Beauty]

507
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:46,076
I don't think I need to learn this!

508
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:47,143
I'll get going now.

509
00:28:47,167 --> 00:28:48,443
Hey!

510
00:28:48,467 --> 00:28:50,676
This isn't a skill I teach
to just anyone, you know?

511
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:52,909
Aren't you pissed off
that your face ended up like this?

512
00:28:52,933 --> 00:28:54,976
You're pissed off, right?

513
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,409
Stay still, or you'll get hurt.

514
00:28:58,433 --> 00:29:01,133
Hey, be honest. You're pissed, right?

515
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,676
That's it! Hey, give me more!

516
00:29:06,700 --> 00:29:07,709
More!

517
00:29:07,733 --> 00:29:09,476
Pretend someone stole your food!

518
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:12,443
My chicken!

519
00:29:12,467 --> 00:29:14,633
Okay.

520
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:17,267
Well done.

521
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:21,233
Ugh, my eyes hurt.

522
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:29,467
Don't be scared if you did nothing wrong.

523
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:49,733
What? Is he insane?

524
00:30:00,267 --> 00:30:02,733
Don't be scared if you did nothing wrong.

525
00:30:08,233 --> 00:30:10,276
Yeah, he is right.

526
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:12,176
There's no reason to cry over this.

527
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:15,133
They're the bad ones. What did I do wrong?

528
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:19,467
The lenses.

529
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:25,843
Right, this is more like me.

530
00:30:25,867 --> 00:30:29,200
A brave Korean high school girl!

531
00:30:34,133 --> 00:30:36,667
Glasses are definitely more comfortable.

532
00:30:38,467 --> 00:30:42,543
[Koo Seon Ho: U Yeon, are you on your way?]

533
00:30:42,567 --> 00:30:45,300
[Yes, I'm heading there.]

534
00:30:46,633 --> 00:30:48,376
Ah, this isn't good! Hey, call him again!

535
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,176
That Poo Gi Jeong! Did he die
in the toilet or something?

536
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:52,033
Okay. I got it.

537
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:55,376
There he is.

538
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:56,976
I really want to kill him.

539
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,643
Do you even know what time it is?

540
00:30:59,667 --> 00:31:02,076
Oh, no. Were you waiting?

541
00:31:02,100 --> 00:31:04,776
I waited forever!

542
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,009
What's up with you guys?

543
00:31:06,033 --> 00:31:07,076
Why are you all dressed up?

544
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:09,309
You said you'd buy me meat today!

545
00:31:09,333 --> 00:31:10,376
Were you lying?

546
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:13,643
I'll buy it, I said I would!

547
00:31:13,667 --> 00:31:14,909
Hey, hey!

548
